British Airways flight 2652 from Gatwick to Salzburg has been abruptly diverted back to the UK. The reason behind the sudden diversion and return to Gatwick remains unclear. At the scene, emergency services were seen surrounding the plane on the tarmac. Sky News' commentator Alastair Bruce noted the flight journey and filmed the plane stuck on the tarmac. He tweeted: "Interesting BA 2652 to Salzburg returns & surrounded by emergency services at Gatwick. Anyone know what happened?" According to Flight Aware, the plane left Gatwick at 7:14am and did not even make it to the sea before looping around and returning to the airport. The flight was in the air for 1:40 minutes before landing at Gatwick at 8:55am. JUST IN: Nicola Bulley's dog was probably in fight or flight mode, expert says   We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express 